Python library dependencies for AWS Lambda. 

1. Create the zip
Create a folder called python:
$ mkdir python
$ cd python

Install the Python libraries you need in there. You can do this either with a single library:
$ pip install --target . requests
or with a list of libraries (requirements.txt)

$ pip install --target . -r requirements.txt
finally, zip up everything.

Zip the file:
$ zip -r dependencies.zip ../python

2. Create a layer in the AWS console.

3. Add the layer to the lambda function

Credits:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46991117/aws-python-lambda-functionno-module-named-requests/64462403#64462403


